<!---------------------------->
<table cellpadding=2 cellspacing=2>
<tr><td valign="top"><b>Recommended Level<br>for starting quest:</b></td><td valign="bottom"> 45<br></td></tr>
<tr><td valign="top"><b>Starting zone:</b></td><td valign="top"> Wakening Lands<br></td></tr>
<tr><td valign="top"><b>Additional zones:</b></td><td valign="top"> -<br></td></tr>
<tr><td valign="top"><b>Starting NPC:</b></td><td valign="top"> None<br></td></tr>
<tr><td valign="top"><b>Reward:</b></td><td valign="top"> Sentient Armor<br><br></td></tr>
</table>

This is not so much a quest as it is an easy way to obtain good Shadow Knight only armor.  The Suits of Sentient armor in the Wakening Lands tower about twice the height of a Troll or Ogre, but are still hard to see because their armor blends in with the yellow, brown, and green of the Jungle.<br>
<br>
The Suits of Armor themselves are around level 45 and probably have about 5000 hit points.  They are very difficult to solo for a Shadow Knight though because they are <b>IMMUNE TO FEAR</b>.  That means your primary means of soloing was just taken away.  They do give a reasonable amount of experience though, and the armor will drop about 5-10% of the time.<br>

